{"title_page": "FIFA 18", "text_new": "{{About|the video game|the tournament|2018 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{long plot|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = FIFA 18\n| image = FIFA18cover.png\n| caption = PlayStation 4 cover art featuring [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]\n| developer = [[EA Vancouver]]<br />EA Romania<ref name=\"EA\">{{cite web|url=http://investor.ea.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=1042147|title=The World's Game EA SPORTS FIFA 33 Available Worldwide Today|work= Electronic Arts Inc.|date=29 September 2017|accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref>\n| publisher = [[EA Sports]]\n| composer = [[Junkie XL]]\n| series = [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'']]\n| engine = [[Frostbite (game engine)|Frostbite 3]] <small>([[PlayStation 4|PS4]], [[Xbox One|X1]], [[Personal computer|PC]])</small>\n| platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]]<br />[[Nintendo Switch]]<br />[[PlayStation 3]]<br />[[PlayStation 4]]<br />[[Xbox 360]]<br />[[Xbox One]]\n| released = 29 September 2017\n| genre = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n| producer = \n}}\n\n'''''FIFA 18''''' is a [[association football|football]] [[simulation video game|simulation]] video game in the [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'' series]], developed and published by [[Electronic Arts]] and was released worldwide on 29 September 2017 for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]] and [[Nintendo Switch]]. It is the 25th instalment in the FIFA series. Portuguese footballer [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] appears as the cover athlete of the regular edition; Portugese footballer [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] appears on the cover of the Icon edition of the game.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n\n''FIFA 18'' is the second instalment in the series to use the [[Frostbite (game engine)|Frostbite 3]] [[game engine]], although some versions of the game use a different game engine. The PlayStation 4, Microsoft Windows and Xbox One versions include a continuation of \"The Journey\" a story-based mode that was originally in ''[[FIFA 17]]'' titled \"The Journey: Hunter Returns\". The PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 versions, known as ''FIFA 18: Legacy Edition'', do not contain any new gameplay features aside from updated kits and squads.<ref>[https://www.easports.com/fifa/news/2017/fifa-18-legacy-faq \"What Is FIFA 18 Legacy Edition? \u2013 FAQ\"]. EA Sports.</ref>\n\n== Gameplay ==\n\n\n\n''FIFA 18'' is a [[sports game]] that simulates association football. The game features 52 fully licensed stadiums from 12 countries, including new stadiums, plus 30 generic fields for a total of 82. All 20 [[Premier League]] stadia are represented in the series.<ref name=SGFIFA>{{cite news|title=FIFA 18: Every Stadium in the Game |url= http://beta.goal.com/en-us/news/fifa-18-every-stadium-in-the-game/1cirxr6ztvmt31jh1j8bp0uie7 |issue=30 June 2017|publisher= Goal.com}}</ref> Commentary is once again provided by [[Martin Tyler]] and [[Alan Smith (footballer, born 1962)|Alan Smith]] with [[Alan McInally]] (in-game score updates), [[Geoff Shreeves]] (injury reports) and Mike West (classified results).\n`\n''FIFA 18'' Ultimate Team Icons, the new version of what has previously been called Legends is playable on the PS4, Xbox One and PC versions of the game.<ref name=THF18>{{cite web | title= EA Sports announce four new FIFA 18 Ultimate Team Icons including Diego Maradona and Thierry Henry | work= Daily Mirror | url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/fifa-18-ultimate-team-icons-10611556 | accessdate=22 June 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Gameplay Trailer, Pre-Order, Icons, PS4, Xbox One, Switch, Ultimate Team, Ronaldo Cover Star \u2013 Everything we Know and Want |url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/fifa-18-release-date-pre-order-ps4-xbox-one-switch-ultimate-team-everything-we-know-19-06-2017 |publisher=usgamer}}</ref> [[Diego Maradona]] was added as a legend to the Ultimate Team, joining Brazilian stars [[Pel\u00e9]] and [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], Russian goalkeeper [[Lev Yashin]], and French star [[Thierry Henry]] for the 95-rated card.<ref>[https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/ea-sports-add-diego-maradona-to-fifa-18-with-95rated-card-a3599761.html \"FIFA 18 to include 95-rated icon Diego Maradona as EA Sports adds footballing legend to Ultimate Team\"]. ''London Evening Standard''. Retrieved 8 September 2017</ref> New [[goal celebration]]s featured include [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]'s \"Siii\" jump (accompanied with a voiceover from Ronaldo), [[Wayne Rooney]]'s \"Knockout\", [[Samuel Eto'o]]'s \"Old Man\" routine, [[Robert Lewandowski]]'s \"X\", and [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]] kissing his ring finger.<ref>{{cite news |title=How to do the 12 new FIFA 18 celebrations \u2013 plus more of our favourites |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/how-do-12-new-fifa-18-celebrations-plus-more-our-favourites?page=0%2C2 |accessdate=11 October 2018 |work=FourFourTwo}}</ref> The [[Cruyff turn]] \u2013 a [[Dummy (football)#Association football|feint]] named after 1970s Dutch star [[Johan Cruyff]] \u2013 is one of the four new skills added to the game.<ref>{{cite news |title=FIFA 18 Skill Moves: How to do all the new and five-star skills |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/fifa-18-skill-moves-how-to-do-all-the-new-and-five-star/1xcjbpvssnux41u1axq64chstr |accessdate=1 November 2018 |work=Goal}}</ref>\n\n''FIFA 18'' features the third tier of Germany's [[Bundesliga]], the [[3. Liga]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/fifa-18-to-include-german-3liga-for-first-time-in-series/1akvwovqfvw1i1ocot9siybb30|title=FIFA 18 to include German 3. Liga for first time in series |website=Goal.com|access-date=10 September 2017}}</ref> It also features the [[Iceland national football team]], the [[Saudi Arabia national football team]], both the [[New Zealand national football team|men's]] and [[New Zealand women's national football team|women's]] national New Zealand teams, and has again included the [[S\u00fcper Lig|Turkish Super League]] after EA renewed its licence with them.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/iceland-national-team-included-in-fifa-18/d5zdq5qgnjzw1si4aul1969em|title=Iceland national team included in FIFA 18 |website=Goal.com|access-date=10 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/football/2017/08/23/turkish-super-league-renews-license-for-fifa-18|title=Turkish Super League renews license for FIFA 18|work=DailySabah|access-date=10 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[EA Sports]] have introduced Quick Subs into ''FIFA 18'' where the player can make a substitute when the ball goes out of play.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dreamteamfc.com/c/gaming/229518/fifa-18-ea-sports-announce-introduction-of-quick-subs/|title=FIFA 18: EA Sports announce introduction of 'quick subs'|date=10 June 2017|work=Dream Team FC|access-date=25 September 2017}}</ref> Also now in Career Mode players can watch interactive transfer negotiations happen and can also see their new signings unveiled in cut scenes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/fifa-18-career-mode-everything-you-need-to-know/q7bqakljjuhu10ssv82rxwwaa|title=FIFA 18 Career mode: Everything you need to know |website=Goal.com|access-date=25 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n== ''The Journey: Hunter Returns'' ==\nThe story-based Journey mode that was introduced in ''[[FIFA 17]]'' returns in this instalment and continues the narrative under the title \"The Journey: Hunter Returns\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/fifa-17s-new-story-mode-wont-be-in-xbox-360-ps3-ve/1100-6440721/|title=FIFA 17's New Story Mode Won't Be in Xbox 360, PS3 Versions|first=Tamoor|last=Hussain|date=12 June 2016|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref><ref name=AFF>{{cite web|url= http://m.goal.com/s/en/news/1688/goal-gaming/2017/06/19/36484852/the-journey-in-fifa-18-alex-hunters-story-so-far-what-to |title= The Journey in FIFA 18: Alex Hunter's Story So Far & What to Expect in Season Two |date=21 June 2017|publisher=Goal.com}}</ref> If one completed the original story, they will begin ''FIFA 18'' at the same club \u2013 with traits and honours, such as a [[Premier League]] title or [[FA Cup]] win, being carried over. As for those starting fresh, they will see a montage of key plot points in the game, then be able to select from any current English Premier League side. [[Alex Hunter (character)|Alex Hunter]], the 18-year-old main character from [[Clapham]], London, returns and is fully customisable.{{cn|date=January 2020}} Players can unlock items which include new clothes and hairstyles for Hunter. While ''FIFA 17'' locked Hunter to the English Premier League and Championship, in ''FIFA 18'' players can now experience new locations, such as Brazil and the United States.<ref name=AFF/><ref name=CRAH>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/fifa-18-release-date-demo-10608206#14980760502672&|title= When is FIFA 18 out? Cristiano Ronaldo on the cover, Alex Hunter in Journey 2 and full UK release details|date=21 June 2017|work=[[Daily Mirror]]}}</ref> The trailer released for this game mode also shows numerous widely known football players making an appearance such as [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], [[Antoine Griezmann]], [[Dele Alli]], [[Thomas M\u00fcller]], [[Gyasi Zardes]], [[Rio Ferdinand]] and [[Thierry Henry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/9/2/16246078/fifa-18-story-mode-trailer-the-journey-hunter-returns |title=FIFA 18's story mode goes heavy on the special guest stars |last=Good |first=Owen S. |date=2 September 2017 |access-date=13 October 2017}}</ref> NBA player [[James Harden]] is also featured in the trailer and on the video game itself. [[Alex Morgan]] and [[Megan Rapinoe]] also make cameo appearances. The story mode also has new playable characters, such as Danny Williams, who is Alex Hunter's best friend, and also featuring a character new to the series, Alex Hunter's [[half-sister]], Kim Hunter.\n\n===Story===\nThe story begins with a TV-style 'previously on' section that recaps the key events of the first journey. Then the game cuts to Alex Hunter and his friend Danny Williams, enjoying their last day on holiday in Brazil, before they are approached by some young kids who challenge them to a football game. After returning home to England, Alex and his team are informed about a pre-season tournament in the US, before which Alex is invited to an interview with [[Rio Ferdinand]], but later runs into his old friend and rival Gareth Walker, who says he can't believe that Alex is still with his agent Michael Taylor. Then at the tour in LA, Alex's team faces off against [[Real Madrid]] and at the end of the match, regardless of the result, Alex swaps numbers with [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], who suggests that Alex comes and plays for Madrid, having been impressed by his play. If the player beats Real Madrid, you play against LA Galaxy, where Hunter encounters [[Gyasi Zardes]] in the tunnel before the match starts. Alex also meets his father during the tour, and begrudgingly accepts an invitation to have dinner with him. After the tour, Alex Hunter and his teammates go to Chicago where they participate in the [[Major League Soccer All-Star Game|MLS All-Star Game]].\n\nFollowing the first game of the new [[Premier League]] season, Michael tells Alex that none other than Real Madrid are keen on signing him. Despite it being a risky move with Alex who is still in his youth, he decides to follow his dreams, and put forward a transfer request. This causes both Alex's teammates and the fans to lose faith in his commitment to the team \u2013 even to the point of the fans booing him when he is subbed on during a game. Unfortunately, just one day before the transfer window closes, Michael reveals that he found out that the Real Madrid deal was a scam, and that they were never interested in him joining their team. While the club executive appreciates that neither Michael or Alex had any reason to believe the deal was fake, it doesn't counter the fact that Alex put a transfer request in \u2013 meaning that he wanted to leave. Alex is subsequently pulled from the senior squad and put on the youth squad. With just hours until the deadline, Michael admits that he really wanted to sign Alex with Madrid because he was falling behind in his reputation as an agent, and so he went with the deal without really thinking too much. Alex is enraged at Michael for gambling his football career for his personal gain, and the player is then given the option to forgive Michael and stay with him, or fire him due to his almost career ending mistake.\n\nRegardless of the player's decision, Alex then gets a call from his Dad, who is now working for [[LA Galaxy]]. The team offer him a contract to play for LA, due to some injuries their strikers have suffered from. With no other option to go for, aside from training with the youth squad, Alex accepts the deal, helping the team to reach the playoffs. Shortly after he arrives in the US, a young girl recognizes him in the changing rooms. While dining out with his father, Alex learns that she is Kim Hunter \u2013 his half sister. Less than impressed with his father for not telling him about Kim, Alex storms off, but later comes to support Kim during her international debut for the [[United States women's national soccer team|US ladies]] against Germany. With Christmas coming around, Alex returns home to England after the season with LA ends, but gives Kim their grandfather's football for luck in her future games.\n\nAfter reuniting with Danny, who signed up with Alex's former club when he left, Alex learns that [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]], [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|PSG]], and [[Bayern Munich]] are interested in signing him (if the player kept Michael, he signs him or if the player fired him, Alex is signed by his dad). Alex signs to one of them and when he arrives finds out that Dino, the manager of Alex's former loan club, is at his new club as well. Dino pairs Alex up with either [[Thomas Muller]], [[Antoine Griezmann]], or [[Dele Alli]], the player serving as Alex's strike partner. Just three games in however, Alex suffers a knee injury that sidelines him from the pitch for most of the season. At this point the game switches to Danny Williams' perspective, whose career at Alex's former club is at risk. After playing a game, the player is given the option to either play as Williams and try and save his career, or simply give it up and take control of Hunter in the next chapter.\n\nHaving recovered from his injury in rehab, Alex meets up with Kim for a kick around before going back to his European team, where he finds out that Dino's job is at risk, and he may be fired if the club doesn't win any silverware by the season's end. If Hunter plays well and wins the league or cup final, Dino keeps his job. If not, Dino will indeed be fired and Alex helps him clean out his desk.\n\nAfter the season ends, Alex takes Jim over to the US to meet Kim for the first time and they dine at the restaurant. After he eats, Alex receives a call from an agent who claims to have been keeping her eye on him. She offers to make him an icon and tells him to meet up with her, leading into his appearance in [[FIFA 19]].\n\n==Development==\n''FIFA 18'' was developed and published by [[Electronic Arts]]. In January 2017, during the [[Nintendo Switch]] Presentation, EA announced a custom-built port of ''FIFA 18'' on the Nintendo Switch console. It runs on an internally developed [[game engine]], as opposed to [[Frostbite (game engine)|Frostbite engine]] that several versions of the game run on. While the Switch version includes a career mode, it excludes the story-based Journey mode. The Switch version runs at a resolution of 1080p at 60 frames per second when docked to a TV, and 720p at 60 frames per second in the handheld/tabletop mode. The Switch version marks the first time Ultimate Team ever made an appearance on a Nintendo system. Features exclusive to the Switch version include local multiplayer in the form of the new mode Local Seasons, allowing up to 2 Nintendo Switches to connect and compete in a five-match sequence. Another mode exclusive to Switch is the Switch Kick-Off mode, allowing players to instantly get into local/solo matches.<ref name=\"NLcitesAdvNSFIFA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2017/06/fifa_18_on_switch_to_include_ultimate_team_ea_boasts_of_most_advanced_portable_version |title=FIFA 18 on Switch to Include Ultimate Team, EA Boasts of Most 'Advanced' Portable Version |first=Thomas |last=Whitehead |date=10 June 2017 |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |accessdate= 24 June 2017}}</ref><ref name=F18>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-06-11-fifa-18-on-nintendo-switch-is-the-best-portable-fifa-ever |title=FIFA 18 on Nintendo Switch is the best portable FIFA ever|date=21 June 2017|publisher=Wesley Yin-Poole}}</ref>\n\nThe faces for [[Forest Green Rovers]] were captured for the game, a first for a club outside of Europe's top leagues. EA chose the club after they were promoted to the [[English Football League|Football League]] after a 128-year wait.<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/forest-green-rovers-become-first-10905706 \"Forest Green Rovers become first club outside Europe's top leagues to have players' faces captured in FIFA 18\"]. Daily Mirror. Retrieved 8 September 2017</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''FIFA 18'' was released worldwide on 29 September 2017 for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]] and [[Nintendo Switch]].<ref name=FIFA>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/fifa-18-release-date-trailer-the-journey-2-details-and-everything-you-need-to-know/|title=FIFA 18 \u2013 release date, trailer, The Journey 2 details and everything you need to know|work=gamesradar|access-date=11 June 2017}}</ref> [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] is featured on the cover of the game's retail box.<ref name=CR7>{{cite news|url= http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fifa-18-trailer-cristiano-ronaldo-13144615|title=FIFA 18 trailer released with Cristiano Ronaldo the face of the game |date=21 June 2017|newspaper=[[Liverpool Echo]]}}</ref><ref name=CR11>{{cite web|url= http://m.goal.com/s/en/news/1688/goal-gaming/2017/06/20/36135492/fifa-18-xbox-one-and-ps4-release-dates-cost-pre-order-and |title= FIFA 18: Xbox One and PS4 Release Dates, Cost, Pre-order and Complete Guide as Cristiano Ronaldo Bags the Cover |date=21 June 2017|publisher=Goal.com}}</ref>\n\n===Downloadable content===\n{{see also|FIFA World Cup video games#FIFA 18 DLC (Russia '18)}}\nOn 30 April 2018, EA announced a free [[expansion pack|expansion]] based on the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], featuring all 32 participating teams (and the national teams already featured in FIFA 18) and all 12 stadiums used at the 2018 FIFA World Cup as well as the ability for players to create their own customized World Cup tournaments. It was released on 29 May 2018 for the PC, Nintendo Switch, PlayStation 4 and Xbox One versions of the game, with FIFA Mobile getting the mode for a limited time only on 6 June 2018.<ref>https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-04-30-fifa-18-gets-free-world-cup-mode-this-month</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = 84/100 (XONE)<ref name=\"MetaXbox\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for Xbox One Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><br /> 84/100 (PS4)<ref name=\"MetaPS4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for PlayStation 4 Reviews|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=8 December 2017}}</ref><br /> 81/100 (PC)<ref name=\"MetaPC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for PC Reviews|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref><br /> 68/100 (NS)<ref name=\"MetaSwitch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for Switch Reviews|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref>\n| GI = 8.75/10<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kato|first=Matthew|date=21 September 2017|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/fifa_18/b/playstation4/archive/2017/09/21/game-informer-review-fifa-18.aspx|title=FIFA 18: Alex Hunter Makes His Mark Again|magazine=[[Game Informer]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| GameRev = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=GRev>{{cite web|last=Tamburro|first=Paul|date=20 September 2017|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/348565-fifa-18-review-the-greatest-fifa-in-years|title=FIFA 18 Review \u2013 The Greatest FIFA in Years|publisher=[[Game Revolution]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| GSpot = 7/10<ref name=gspot>{{cite web|last=Dayus|first=Oscar|date=21 September 2017|url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/fifa-18-review/1900-6416764/|title=FIFA 18 Review|website=[[GameSpot]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| GRadar = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=GRadar>{{cite web|last=Wilson|first=Ben|date=28 September 2017|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/fifa-18-review/|title=FIFA 18 review|publisher=[[GamesRadar]]|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref>\n| IGN = 8.1/10<ref name=\"IGN\">{{cite web|last=Robertson|first=John|date=20 September 2017|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/09/21/fifa-18-review|title=FIFA 18 Review (PC, PS4, XOne)|website=[[IGN]]|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><br/>(NS) 5.5/10<ref name=\"IGNNS\">{{cite web|last=Robertson|first=John|date=10 October 2017|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/10/fifa-18-switch-review|title=FIFA 18 Switch Review|website=IGN|accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref> \n}}\n''FIFA 18'' received \"generally favourable\" reviews for the PS4,<ref name=\"MetaPS4\"/> Xbox One<ref name=\"MetaXbox\"/> and PC<ref name=\"MetaPC\"/> versions of the game, while the Nintendo Switch version received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics,<ref name=\"MetaSwitch\"/> according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].\n\nIn their review scoring 7 out of 10, [[GameSpot]] wrote, \"From the variety of game modes on offer and how everything's presented, to the constant updates in FUT's Team of the Week, Daily Objectives, and discussion of real-world happenings in commentary, ''FIFA 18'' captures the world of football and confidently translates it into a video game. On the pitch, however, EA's soccer series is still lagging far behind ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2018|PES 2018]]''{{'}}s more fluid, satisfying football.\"<ref name=gspot/> [[IGN]] gave it an 8.1/10, saying, \"A sharp focus on attack but few new additions make this a spectacular if somewhat shallow experience.\"<ref name=IGN/>\n\n^=== Accolades ===\n''[[Eurogamer]]'' ranked the game 30th on their list of the \"Top 50 Games of 2017\".<ref>{{cite web|date=28 December 2017|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-12-28-eurogamers-top-50-games-of-2017-30-21|title=Eurogamer's Top 50 Games of 2017: 30\u201321|website=[[Eurogamer]]|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref> The game won the award for \"Best Sports Game\" at the 2017 [[Game Critics Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamecriticsawards.com/winners.html|title=Game Critics Awards: Best of E3 2017 (2017 Winners)|work=[[Game Critics Awards]]|accessdate=20 January 2018|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6QkQhZDfX?url=http://www.gamecriticsawards.com/winners.html|archive-date=1 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and was nominated for \"Best Console Game (Nintendo Switch)\" and \"Best Sports Game\" at the [[Gamescom]] 2017 Awards.<ref>{{cite web|last=Khan|first=Zubi|date=21 August 2017|url=http://www.cgmagonline.com/2017/08/21/gamescom-2017-award-nominees/|title=Gamescom 2017 Award Nominees|publisher=CGM|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> It was also nominated for \"Best Multiplayer Game\" at the [[Golden Joystick Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Gaito|first=Eri|date=13 November 2017|url=https://www.bestinslot.co/golden-joystick-awards-2017-nominees/|title=Golden Joystick Awards 2017 Nominees|publisher=Best in Slot|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> for \"Best Sports/Racing Game\" at [[The Game Awards 2017]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=8 December 2017|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/the-game-awards-2017-winners-headlined-by-zelda-br/1100-6455467/|title=The Game Awards 2017 Winners Headlined By Zelda: Breath Of The Wild's Game Of The Year|website=GameSpot|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> and for \"Best Sports/Driving Game\" at the [[Fun & Serious Game Festival|Titanium Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.funandseriousgamefestival.com/the-list-of-finalists-for-the-fun-serious-titanium-awards-has-been-revealed-2017/|title=The list of finalists for the Fun & Serious Titanium Awards has been revealed|publisher=[[Fun & Serious Game Festival]]|year=2017|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref> It won the award for \"Best Story\" at ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s 2017 Sports Game of the Year Awards,<ref>{{cite magazine|date=8 January 2018|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2018/01/08/the-2017-sports-game-of-the-year-awards.aspx|title=The 2017 Sports Game of the Year Awards|magazine=Game Informer|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> while it took the lead for \"Best Sports Game\" in their Reader's Choice Best of 2017 Awards.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Cork|first=Jeff|date=4 January 2018|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2018/01/04/reader-s-choice-best-of-2017-awards.aspx?PostPageIndex=4|title=Reader's Choice Best Of 2017 Awards (Page 4)|magazine=Game Informer|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> It won the awards for \"Best Music Supervision in a Video Game\" at the [[Guild of Music Supervisors Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Waters|first=Michael|date=9 February 2018|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/guild-music-supervisors-awards-2018-winners-1078504|title=Guild of Music Supervisors Awards: Winners List|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref> and for \"Sports Game of the Year\" at the [[21st Annual D.I.C.E. Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=14 January 2018|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/game-of-the-year-nominees-announced-for-dice-award/1100-6456107/|title=Game of the Year Nominees Announced For DICE Awards|website=GameSpot|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=22 February 2018|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/legend-of-zelda-breath-of-the-wild-wins-game-of-th/1100-6456956/|title=Legend Of Zelda: Breath Of The Wild Wins Game Of The Year At DICE Awards|website=GameSpot|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref> and was nominated for \"Game, Franchise Sports\" at the 17th Annual [[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]] Awards,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/|title=Nominee List for 2017|publisher=[[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]]|date=9 February 2018|accessdate=18 February 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180215172210/http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/|archive-date=15 February 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/|title=Horizon wins 7; Mario GOTY|publisher=National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers|date=13 March 2018|accessdate=14 March 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180314070824/http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/|archive-date=14 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> and for \"eSports Game of the Year\" at the 2018 [[SXSW Gaming Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|last=McNeill|first=Andrew|date=31 January 2018|url=https://gaming.sxsw.com/news/2018/2018-sxsw-gaming-awards-finalists/|title=Here Are Your 2018 SXSW Gaming Awards Finalists!|publisher=[[South by Southwest|SXSW]]|accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=IGN Studios|date=17 March 2018|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/03/18/sxsw-gaming-awards-2018-winners-revealed|title=2018 SXSW Gaming Awards Winners Revealed|website=[[IGN]]|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> It won the award for \"Best Selling Game\" at the Italian Video Game Awards, whereas its other nomination was for \"People's Choice\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://italianvideogameawards.com/awards|title=Italian Video Game Nominees and Winners 2018|publisher=Italian Video Game Awards|date=14 March 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321193010/https://italianvideogameawards.com/awards|archivedate=21 March 2018|url-status=dead|accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref> It was also nominated for \"Best Game\" at [[BBC Radio 1|BBC Radio 1's Teen Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2018/radio-1s-teen-awards|title=Little Mix, 5 Seconds Of Summer, Sigrid and Jonas Blue lead the performances for BBC Radio 1's Teen Awards 2018|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=10 September 2018|accessdate=7 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Sales ===\nIn September 2018, EA Sports announced that the game sold more than 24 million with all of its versions.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Valentine |first1=Rebekah |title=FIFA 18 sells over 24 million copies |url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-09-05-fifa-18-sells-over-24-million-copies |website=Gamesindustry |accessdate=5 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Controversy ===\n''FIFA 18'' faced a backlash from fans due to its bugs and [[microtransaction]]s system in Ultimate Team mode which makes it [[pay-to-win]] resulting in a Black Friday boycott by fans in November 2017 and a petition being launched by fans with the [[hashtag]] #FixFifa. Players criticized EA of changing the game through patches which resulted in large amounts of glitches and bugs in the game, players not getting what they paid for, and the need to spend a large amount of real currency to obtain a decent Ultimate Team. FIFA Ultimate Team packs have been called [[loot box]]es in another name and the similarity to addictive gambling due to their use of variable-ratio scheduling used in gambling. Players also accused Ultimate Team packs of having mediocre drop rates. ''FIFA 18'', alongside several other EA games such as ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II (2017 video game)|Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'', are also under investigation by countries such as Belgium for their loot box systems.<ref>{{cite news|title=FIFA 18 Ultimate Team Microtransactions Cause Fan Uproar|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/11/23/fifa-18-ultimate-team-microtransactions-cause-fan-uproar|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=FIFA 18 fans organize Black Friday in-game purchase boycott|url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/11/23/16694776/fifa-18-fans-organize-black-friday-in-game-purchase-boycott|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Getting Rid of FIFA Ultimate Team packs Is the BestTthing EA Sports Can Do|url=https://www.dreamteamfc.com/c/gaming/360335/fifa-18-lootbox-release-ultimate-team/|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Micro Transactions System Used in FIFA Ultimate Team, Star Wars Battlefront and Other Popular Games Could Be Banned|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/gaming/micro-transactions-fifa-18-ultimate-team-star-wars-battlefront-banned-belgium-a8070106.html|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n    alt-J (UK) - Deadcrush\n    Avelino (UK) - Energy (con la partecipazione di Skepta e Stormzy)\n    Bad Sounds (UK) - Wages\n    Baloji (Belgio) - L'Hiver Indien\n    B\u00d8RNS (USA) - Faded Heart\n    Capital Cities (USA) - Safe & Sound\n    Cut Copy (AUS) - Standing In The Middle Of The Field (Radio Edit)\n    Django Django (UK) - Tic Tac Toe\n    Dua Lipa (UK) - New Rules\n    Hailee Steinfeld (USA) - Let Me Go\n    Hailee Steinfeld (USA) - Most Girl\n    IDER (UK) - King Ruby\n    Kimbra (NZ) - Top Of The World\n    Kovic (UK) - Drown\n    Lorde (NZ) - Supercut\n    Mondo Cozmo (USA) - Automatic\n    Mura Masa (Guernsey) - Helpline (con la partecipazione di Tom Tripp)\n    ODESZA (USA) - La Ciudad\n    Off Bloom (Danimarca) - Falcon Eye\n    Oliver (CAN/USA) - Heart Attack (con la partecipazione di De La Soul)\n    Outsider (Irlanda) - Miol Mor Mara\n    Perfume Genius (USA) - Slip Away\n    Phantoms (USA) - Throw It In The Fire\n    Portugal. The Man (USA) - Live In The Moment\n    RAC (Portogallo/USA) - Beautiful Game (con la partecipazione di St. Lucia)\n    Residente (Portorico) - Dagombas en Tamale\n    Rex Orange County (UK) - Never Enough\n    Run the Jewels (USA) - Mean Demeanor\n    Sir Sly (USA) - &Run\n    Slowdive (UK) - Star Roving\n    Sneakbo (con la partecipazione di Giggs) (UK) - Active\n    Sofi Tukker (USA) - Best Friend (con la partecipazione di NERVO, The Knocks e Alisa UENO)\n    Superorganism (UK) - Something For Your M.I.N.D.\n    Tash Sultana (Australia) - Jungle\n    T\u00e9m\u00e9 Tan (Belgio) - \u00c7a Va Pas La T\u00eate?\n    The Amazons (UK) - Stay With Me\n    The National (USA) - The System Only Dreams In Total Darkness\n    The War on Drugs (USA) - Holding On\n    The xx (UK) - Dangerous\n    Tom Grennan (UK) - Found What I've Been Looking For\n    Toothless (UK) - Sisyphus\n    Vessels (UK) - Deflect The Light (con la partecipazione di The Flaming Lips)\n    Washed Out (USA) - Get Lost\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.easports.com/fifa}}\n*[https://200gaming.com/fifa-18-pc-game-download/ FIFA 18]\n\n\n{{Football video games by Electronic Arts}}\n{{Women's association football}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games|Association football|Women's association football}}\n\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Association football video games]]\n[[Category:Women's association football video games]]\n[[Category:EA Sports games]]\n[[Category:FIFA (video game series)]]\n[[Category:Frostbite (game engine) games]]\n[[Category:J.League licensed video games]]\n[[Category:La Liga licensed video games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Video games that support DirectX 12]]\n[[Category:Video games containing loot boxes]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in France]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in Germany]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in Italy]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in the United States]]\n[[Category:Sports video games with career mode]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Canada]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Romania]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch eShop games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 3 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 Pro enhanced games]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox 360 games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Diego Maradona]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Pel\u00e9]]\n[[Category:Works by Junkie XL]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the video game|the tournament|2018 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{long plot|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = FIFA 18\n| image = FIFA18cover.png\n| caption = PlayStation 4 cover art featuring [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]\n| developer = [[EA Vancouver]]<br />EA Romania<ref name=\"EA\">{{cite web|url=http://investor.ea.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=1042147|title=The World's Game EA SPORTS FIFA 33 Available Worldwide Today|work= Electronic Arts Inc.|date=29 September 2017|accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref>\n| publisher = [[EA Sports]]\n| composer = [[Junkie XL]]\n| series = [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'']]\n| engine = [[Frostbite (game engine)|Frostbite 3]] <small>([[PlayStation 4|PS4]], [[Xbox One|X1]], [[Personal computer|PC]])</small>\n| platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]]<br />[[Nintendo Switch]]<br />[[PlayStation 3]]<br />[[PlayStation 4]]<br />[[Xbox 360]]<br />[[Xbox One]]\n| released = 29 September 2017\n| genre = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n| producer = \n}}\n\n'''''FIFA 18''''' is a [[association football|football]] [[simulation video game|simulation]] video game in the [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'' series]], developed and published by [[Electronic Arts]] and was released worldwide on 29 September 2017 for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]] and [[Nintendo Switch]]. It is the 25th instalment in the FIFA series. Portuguese footballer [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] appears as the cover athlete of the regular edition; Portugese footballer [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] appears on the cover of the Icon edition of the game.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n\n''FIFA 18'' is the second instalment in the series to use the [[Frostbite (game engine)|Frostbite 3]] [[game engine]], although some versions of the game use a different game engine. The PlayStation 4, Microsoft Windows and Xbox One versions include a continuation of \"The Journey\" a story-based mode that was originally in ''[[FIFA 17]]'' titled \"The Journey: Hunter Returns\". The PlayStation 3 and Xbox 360 versions, known as ''FIFA 18: Legacy Edition'', do not contain any new gameplay features aside from updated kits and squads.<ref>[https://www.easports.com/fifa/news/2017/fifa-18-legacy-faq \"What Is FIFA 18 Legacy Edition? \u2013 FAQ\"]. EA Sports.</ref>\n\n== Gameplay ==\n\n\n\n''FIFA 18'' is a [[sports game]] that simulates association football. The game features 52 fully licensed stadiums from 12 countries, including new stadiums, plus 30 generic fields for a total of 82. All 20 [[Premier League]] stadia are represented in the series.<ref name=SGFIFA>{{cite news|title=FIFA 18: Every Stadium in the Game |url= http://beta.goal.com/en-us/news/fifa-18-every-stadium-in-the-game/1cirxr6ztvmt31jh1j8bp0uie7 |issue=30 June 2017|publisher= Goal.com}}</ref> Commentary is once again provided by [[Martin Tyler]] and [[Alan Smith (footballer, born 1962)|Alan Smith]] with [[Alan McInally]] (in-game score updates), [[Geoff Shreeves]] (injury reports) and Mike West (classified results).\n`\n''FIFA 18'' Ultimate Team Icons, the new version of what has previously been called Legends is playable on the PS4, Xbox One and PC versions of the game.<ref name=THF18>{{cite web | title= EA Sports announce four new FIFA 18 Ultimate Team Icons including Diego Maradona and Thierry Henry | work= Daily Mirror | url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/fifa-18-ultimate-team-icons-10611556 | accessdate=22 June 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Gameplay Trailer, Pre-Order, Icons, PS4, Xbox One, Switch, Ultimate Team, Ronaldo Cover Star \u2013 Everything we Know and Want |url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/fifa-18-release-date-pre-order-ps4-xbox-one-switch-ultimate-team-everything-we-know-19-06-2017 |publisher=usgamer}}</ref> [[Diego Maradona]] was added as a legend to the Ultimate Team, joining Brazilian stars [[Pel\u00e9]] and [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], Russian goalkeeper [[Lev Yashin]], and French star [[Thierry Henry]] for the 95-rated card.<ref>[https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/ea-sports-add-diego-maradona-to-fifa-18-with-95rated-card-a3599761.html \"FIFA 18 to include 95-rated icon Diego Maradona as EA Sports adds footballing legend to Ultimate Team\"]. ''London Evening Standard''. Retrieved 8 September 2017</ref> New [[goal celebration]]s featured include [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]'s \"Siii\" jump (accompanied with a voiceover from Ronaldo), [[Wayne Rooney]]'s \"Knockout\", [[Samuel Eto'o]]'s \"Old Man\" routine, [[Robert Lewandowski]]'s \"X\", and [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]] kissing his ring finger.<ref>{{cite news |title=How to do the 12 new FIFA 18 celebrations \u2013 plus more of our favourites |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/how-do-12-new-fifa-18-celebrations-plus-more-our-favourites?page=0%2C2 |accessdate=11 October 2018 |work=FourFourTwo}}</ref> The [[Cruyff turn]] \u2013 a [[Dummy (football)#Association football|feint]] named after 1970s Dutch star [[Johan Cruyff]] \u2013 is one of the four new skills added to the game.<ref>{{cite news |title=FIFA 18 Skill Moves: How to do all the new and five-star skills |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/fifa-18-skill-moves-how-to-do-all-the-new-and-five-star/1xcjbpvssnux41u1axq64chstr |accessdate=1 November 2018 |work=Goal}}</ref>\n\n''FIFA 18'' features the third tier of Germany's [[Bundesliga]], the [[3. Liga]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/fifa-18-to-include-german-3liga-for-first-time-in-series/1akvwovqfvw1i1ocot9siybb30|title=FIFA 18 to include German 3. Liga for first time in series |website=Goal.com|access-date=10 September 2017}}</ref> It also features the [[Iceland national football team]], the [[Saudi Arabia national football team]], both the [[New Zealand national football team|men's]] and [[New Zealand women's national football team|women's]] national New Zealand teams, and has again included the [[S\u00fcper Lig|Turkish Super League]] after EA renewed its licence with them.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/iceland-national-team-included-in-fifa-18/d5zdq5qgnjzw1si4aul1969em|title=Iceland national team included in FIFA 18 |website=Goal.com|access-date=10 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/football/2017/08/23/turkish-super-league-renews-license-for-fifa-18|title=Turkish Super League renews license for FIFA 18|work=DailySabah|access-date=10 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[EA Sports]] have introduced Quick Subs into ''FIFA 18'' where the player can make a substitute when the ball goes out of play.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dreamteamfc.com/c/gaming/229518/fifa-18-ea-sports-announce-introduction-of-quick-subs/|title=FIFA 18: EA Sports announce introduction of 'quick subs'|date=10 June 2017|work=Dream Team FC|access-date=25 September 2017}}</ref> Also now in Career Mode players can watch interactive transfer negotiations happen and can also see their new signings unveiled in cut scenes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/fifa-18-career-mode-everything-you-need-to-know/q7bqakljjuhu10ssv82rxwwaa|title=FIFA 18 Career mode: Everything you need to know |website=Goal.com|access-date=25 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n== ''The Journey: Hunter Returns'' ==\nThe story-based Journey mode that was introduced in ''[[FIFA 17]]'' returns in this instalment and continues the narrative under the title \"The Journey: Hunter Returns\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/fifa-17s-new-story-mode-wont-be-in-xbox-360-ps3-ve/1100-6440721/|title=FIFA 17's New Story Mode Won't Be in Xbox 360, PS3 Versions|first=Tamoor|last=Hussain|date=12 June 2016|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref><ref name=AFF>{{cite web|url= http://m.goal.com/s/en/news/1688/goal-gaming/2017/06/19/36484852/the-journey-in-fifa-18-alex-hunters-story-so-far-what-to |title= The Journey in FIFA 18: Alex Hunter's Story So Far & What to Expect in Season Two |date=21 June 2017|publisher=Goal.com}}</ref> If one completed the original story, they will begin ''FIFA 18'' at the same club \u2013 with traits and honours, such as a [[Premier League]] title or [[FA Cup]] win, being carried over. As for those starting fresh, they will see a montage of key plot points in the game, then be able to select from any current English Premier League side. [[Alex Hunter (character)|Alex Hunter]], the 18-year-old main character from [[Clapham]], London, returns and is fully customisable.{{cn|date=January 2020}} Players can unlock items which include new clothes and hairstyles for Hunter. While ''FIFA 17'' locked Hunter to the English Premier League and Championship, in ''FIFA 18'' players can now experience new locations, such as Brazil and the United States.<ref name=AFF/><ref name=CRAH>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/fifa-18-release-date-demo-10608206#14980760502672&|title= When is FIFA 18 out? Cristiano Ronaldo on the cover, Alex Hunter in Journey 2 and full UK release details|date=21 June 2017|work=[[Daily Mirror]]}}</ref> The trailer released for this game mode also shows numerous widely known football players making an appearance such as [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], [[Antoine Griezmann]], [[Dele Alli]], [[Thomas M\u00fcller]], [[Gyasi Zardes]], [[Rio Ferdinand]] and [[Thierry Henry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/9/2/16246078/fifa-18-story-mode-trailer-the-journey-hunter-returns |title=FIFA 18's story mode goes heavy on the special guest stars |last=Good |first=Owen S. |date=2 September 2017 |access-date=13 October 2017}}</ref> NBA player [[James Harden]] is also featured in the trailer and on the video game itself. [[Alex Morgan]] and [[Megan Rapinoe]] also make cameo appearances. The story mode also has new playable characters, such as Danny Williams, who is Alex Hunter's best friend, and also featuring a character new to the series, Alex Hunter's [[half-sister]], Kim Hunter.\n\n===Story===\nThe story begins with a TV-style 'previously on' section that recaps the key events of the first journey. Then the game cuts to Alex Hunter and his friend Danny Williams, enjoying their last day on holiday in Brazil, before they are approached by some young kids who challenge them to a football game. After returning home to England, Alex and his team are informed about a pre-season tournament in the US, before which Alex is invited to an interview with [[Rio Ferdinand]], but later runs into his old friend and rival Gareth Walker, who says he can't believe that Alex is still with his agent Michael Taylor. Then at the tour in LA, Alex's team faces off against [[Real Madrid]] and at the end of the match, regardless of the result, Alex swaps numbers with [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], who suggests that Alex comes and plays for Madrid, having been impressed by his play. If the player beats Real Madrid, you play against LA Galaxy, where Hunter encounters [[Gyasi Zardes]] in the tunnel before the match starts. Alex also meets his father during the tour, and begrudgingly accepts an invitation to have dinner with him. After the tour, Alex Hunter and his teammates go to Chicago where they participate in the [[Major League Soccer All-Star Game|MLS All-Star Game]].\n\nFollowing the first game of the new [[Premier League]] season, Michael tells Alex that none other than Real Madrid are keen on signing him. Despite it being a risky move with Alex who is still in his youth, he decides to follow his dreams, and put forward a transfer request. This causes both Alex's teammates and the fans to lose faith in his commitment to the team \u2013 even to the point of the fans booing him when he is subbed on during a game. Unfortunately, just one day before the transfer window closes, Michael reveals that he found out that the Real Madrid deal was a scam, and that they were never interested in him joining their team. While the club executive appreciates that neither Michael or Alex had any reason to believe the deal was fake, it doesn't counter the fact that Alex put a transfer request in \u2013 meaning that he wanted to leave. Alex is subsequently pulled from the senior squad and put on the youth squad. With just hours until the deadline, Michael admits that he really wanted to sign Alex with Madrid because he was falling behind in his reputation as an agent, and so he went with the deal without really thinking too much. Alex is enraged at Michael for gambling his football career for his personal gain, and the player is then given the option to forgive Michael and stay with him, or fire him due to his almost career ending mistake.\n\nRegardless of the player's decision, Alex then gets a call from his Dad, who is now working for [[LA Galaxy]]. The team offer him a contract to play for LA, due to some injuries their strikers have suffered from. With no other option to go for, aside from training with the youth squad, Alex accepts the deal, helping the team to reach the playoffs. Shortly after he arrives in the US, a young girl recognizes him in the changing rooms. While dining out with his father, Alex learns that she is Kim Hunter \u2013 his half sister. Less than impressed with his father for not telling him about Kim, Alex storms off, but later comes to support Kim during her international debut for the [[United States women's national soccer team|US ladies]] against Germany. With Christmas coming around, Alex returns home to England after the season with LA ends, but gives Kim their grandfather's football for luck in her future games.\n\nAfter reuniting with Danny, who signed up with Alex's former club when he left, Alex learns that [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]], [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|PSG]], and [[Bayern Munich]] are interested in signing him (if the player kept Michael, he signs him or if the player fired him, Alex is signed by his dad). Alex signs to one of them and when he arrives finds out that Dino, the manager of Alex's former loan club, is at his new club as well. Dino pairs Alex up with either [[Thomas Muller]], [[Antoine Griezmann]], or [[Dele Alli]], the player serving as Alex's strike partner. Just three games in however, Alex suffers a knee injury that sidelines him from the pitch for most of the season. At this point the game switches to Danny Williams' perspective, whose career at Alex's former club is at risk. After playing a game, the player is given the option to either play as Williams and try and save his career, or simply give it up and take control of Hunter in the next chapter.\n\nHaving recovered from his injury in rehab, Alex meets up with Kim for a kick around before going back to his European team, where he finds out that Dino's job is at risk, and he may be fired if the club doesn't win any silverware by the season's end. If Hunter plays well and wins the league or cup final, Dino keeps his job. If not, Dino will indeed be fired and Alex helps him clean out his desk.\n\nAfter the season ends, Alex takes Jim over to the US to meet Kim for the first time and they dine at the restaurant. After he eats, Alex receives a call from an agent who claims to have been keeping her eye on him. She offers to make him an icon and tells him to meet up with her, leading into his appearance in [[FIFA 19]].\n\n==Development==\n''FIFA 18'' was developed and published by [[Electronic Arts]]. In January 2017, during the [[Nintendo Switch]] Presentation, EA announced a custom-built port of ''FIFA 18'' on the Nintendo Switch console. It runs on an internally developed [[game engine]], as opposed to [[Frostbite (game engine)|Frostbite engine]] that several versions of the game run on. While the Switch version includes a career mode, it excludes the story-based Journey mode. The Switch version runs at a resolution of 1080p at 60 frames per second when docked to a TV, and 720p at 60 frames per second in the handheld/tabletop mode. The Switch version marks the first time Ultimate Team ever made an appearance on a Nintendo system. Features exclusive to the Switch version include local multiplayer in the form of the new mode Local Seasons, allowing up to 2 Nintendo Switches to connect and compete in a five-match sequence. Another mode exclusive to Switch is the Switch Kick-Off mode, allowing players to instantly get into local/solo matches.<ref name=\"NLcitesAdvNSFIFA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2017/06/fifa_18_on_switch_to_include_ultimate_team_ea_boasts_of_most_advanced_portable_version |title=FIFA 18 on Switch to Include Ultimate Team, EA Boasts of Most 'Advanced' Portable Version |first=Thomas |last=Whitehead |date=10 June 2017 |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |accessdate= 24 June 2017}}</ref><ref name=F18>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-06-11-fifa-18-on-nintendo-switch-is-the-best-portable-fifa-ever |title=FIFA 18 on Nintendo Switch is the best portable FIFA ever|date=21 June 2017|publisher=Wesley Yin-Poole}}</ref>\n\nThe faces for [[Forest Green Rovers]] were captured for the game, a first for a club outside of Europe's top leagues. EA chose the club after they were promoted to the [[English Football League|Football League]] after a 128-year wait.<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/forest-green-rovers-become-first-10905706 \"Forest Green Rovers become first club outside Europe's top leagues to have players' faces captured in FIFA 18\"]. Daily Mirror. Retrieved 8 September 2017</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''FIFA 18'' was released worldwide on 29 September 2017 for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]] and [[Nintendo Switch]].<ref name=FIFA>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/fifa-18-release-date-trailer-the-journey-2-details-and-everything-you-need-to-know/|title=FIFA 18 \u2013 release date, trailer, The Journey 2 details and everything you need to know|work=gamesradar|access-date=11 June 2017}}</ref> [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] is featured on the cover of the game's retail box.<ref name=CR7>{{cite news|url= http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fifa-18-trailer-cristiano-ronaldo-13144615|title=FIFA 18 trailer released with Cristiano Ronaldo the face of the game |date=21 June 2017|newspaper=[[Liverpool Echo]]}}</ref><ref name=CR11>{{cite web|url= http://m.goal.com/s/en/news/1688/goal-gaming/2017/06/20/36135492/fifa-18-xbox-one-and-ps4-release-dates-cost-pre-order-and |title= FIFA 18: Xbox One and PS4 Release Dates, Cost, Pre-order and Complete Guide as Cristiano Ronaldo Bags the Cover |date=21 June 2017|publisher=Goal.com}}</ref>\n\n===Downloadable content===\n{{see also|FIFA World Cup video games#FIFA 18 DLC (Russia '18)}}\nOn 30 April 2018, EA announced a free [[expansion pack|expansion]] based on the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], featuring all 32 participating teams (and the national teams already featured in FIFA 18) and all 12 stadiums used at the 2018 FIFA World Cup as well as the ability for players to create their own customized World Cup tournaments. It was released on 29 May 2018 for the PC, Nintendo Switch, PlayStation 4 and Xbox One versions of the game, with FIFA Mobile getting the mode for a limited time only on 6 June 2018.<ref>https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-04-30-fifa-18-gets-free-world-cup-mode-this-month</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = 84/100 (XONE)<ref name=\"MetaXbox\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for Xbox One Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><br /> 84/100 (PS4)<ref name=\"MetaPS4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for PlayStation 4 Reviews|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=8 December 2017}}</ref><br /> 81/100 (PC)<ref name=\"MetaPC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for PC Reviews|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref><br /> 68/100 (NS)<ref name=\"MetaSwitch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/fifa-18|title=FIFA 18 for Switch Reviews|publisher=Metacritic|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref>\n| GI = 8.75/10<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kato|first=Matthew|date=21 September 2017|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/fifa_18/b/playstation4/archive/2017/09/21/game-informer-review-fifa-18.aspx|title=FIFA 18: Alex Hunter Makes His Mark Again|magazine=[[Game Informer]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| GameRev = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=GRev>{{cite web|last=Tamburro|first=Paul|date=20 September 2017|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/348565-fifa-18-review-the-greatest-fifa-in-years|title=FIFA 18 Review \u2013 The Greatest FIFA in Years|publisher=[[Game Revolution]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| GSpot = 7/10<ref name=gspot>{{cite web|last=Dayus|first=Oscar|date=21 September 2017|url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/fifa-18-review/1900-6416764/|title=FIFA 18 Review|website=[[GameSpot]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| GRadar = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=GRadar>{{cite web|last=Wilson|first=Ben|date=28 September 2017|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/fifa-18-review/|title=FIFA 18 review|publisher=[[GamesRadar]]|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref>\n| IGN = 8.1/10<ref name=\"IGN\">{{cite web|last=Robertson|first=John|date=20 September 2017|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/09/21/fifa-18-review|title=FIFA 18 Review (PC, PS4, XOne)|website=[[IGN]]|accessdate=27 September 2017}}</ref><br/>(NS) 5.5/10<ref name=\"IGNNS\">{{cite web|last=Robertson|first=John|date=10 October 2017|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/10/fifa-18-switch-review|title=FIFA 18 Switch Review|website=IGN|accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref> \n}}\n''FIFA 18'' received \"generally favourable\" reviews for the PS4,<ref name=\"MetaPS4\"/> Xbox One<ref name=\"MetaXbox\"/> and PC<ref name=\"MetaPC\"/> versions of the game, while the Nintendo Switch version received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics,<ref name=\"MetaSwitch\"/> according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].\n\nIn their review scoring 7 out of 10, [[GameSpot]] wrote, \"From the variety of game modes on offer and how everything's presented, to the constant updates in FUT's Team of the Week, Daily Objectives, and discussion of real-world happenings in commentary, ''FIFA 18'' captures the world of football and confidently translates it into a video game. On the pitch, however, EA's soccer series is still lagging far behind ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2018|PES 2018]]''{{'}}s more fluid, satisfying football.\"<ref name=gspot/> [[IGN]] gave it an 8.1/10, saying, \"A sharp focus on attack but few new additions make this a spectacular if somewhat shallow experience.\"<ref name=IGN/>\n\n^=== Accolades ===\n''[[Eurogamer]]'' ranked the game 30th on their list of the \"Top 50 Games of 2017\".<ref>{{cite web|date=28 December 2017|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-12-28-eurogamers-top-50-games-of-2017-30-21|title=Eurogamer's Top 50 Games of 2017: 30\u201321|website=[[Eurogamer]]|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref> The game won the award for \"Best Sports Game\" at the 2017 [[Game Critics Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamecriticsawards.com/winners.html|title=Game Critics Awards: Best of E3 2017 (2017 Winners)|work=[[Game Critics Awards]]|accessdate=20 January 2018|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6QkQhZDfX?url=http://www.gamecriticsawards.com/winners.html|archive-date=1 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and was nominated for \"Best Console Game (Nintendo Switch)\" and \"Best Sports Game\" at the [[Gamescom]] 2017 Awards.<ref>{{cite web|last=Khan|first=Zubi|date=21 August 2017|url=http://www.cgmagonline.com/2017/08/21/gamescom-2017-award-nominees/|title=Gamescom 2017 Award Nominees|publisher=CGM|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref> It was also nominated for \"Best Multiplayer Game\" at the [[Golden Joystick Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Gaito|first=Eri|date=13 November 2017|url=https://www.bestinslot.co/golden-joystick-awards-2017-nominees/|title=Golden Joystick Awards 2017 Nominees|publisher=Best in Slot|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> for \"Best Sports/Racing Game\" at [[The Game Awards 2017]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=8 December 2017|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/the-game-awards-2017-winners-headlined-by-zelda-br/1100-6455467/|title=The Game Awards 2017 Winners Headlined By Zelda: Breath Of The Wild's Game Of The Year|website=GameSpot|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> and for \"Best Sports/Driving Game\" at the [[Fun & Serious Game Festival|Titanium Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.funandseriousgamefestival.com/the-list-of-finalists-for-the-fun-serious-titanium-awards-has-been-revealed-2017/|title=The list of finalists for the Fun & Serious Titanium Awards has been revealed|publisher=[[Fun & Serious Game Festival]]|year=2017|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref> It won the award for \"Best Story\" at ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s 2017 Sports Game of the Year Awards,<ref>{{cite magazine|date=8 January 2018|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2018/01/08/the-2017-sports-game-of-the-year-awards.aspx|title=The 2017 Sports Game of the Year Awards|magazine=Game Informer|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> while it took the lead for \"Best Sports Game\" in their Reader's Choice Best of 2017 Awards.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Cork|first=Jeff|date=4 January 2018|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2018/01/04/reader-s-choice-best-of-2017-awards.aspx?PostPageIndex=4|title=Reader's Choice Best Of 2017 Awards (Page 4)|magazine=Game Informer|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref> It won the awards for \"Best Music Supervision in a Video Game\" at the [[Guild of Music Supervisors Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Waters|first=Michael|date=9 February 2018|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/guild-music-supervisors-awards-2018-winners-1078504|title=Guild of Music Supervisors Awards: Winners List|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref> and for \"Sports Game of the Year\" at the [[21st Annual D.I.C.E. Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=14 January 2018|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/game-of-the-year-nominees-announced-for-dice-award/1100-6456107/|title=Game of the Year Nominees Announced For DICE Awards|website=GameSpot|accessdate=20 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Makuch|first=Eddie|date=22 February 2018|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/legend-of-zelda-breath-of-the-wild-wins-game-of-th/1100-6456956/|title=Legend Of Zelda: Breath Of The Wild Wins Game Of The Year At DICE Awards|website=GameSpot|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref> and was nominated for \"Game, Franchise Sports\" at the 17th Annual [[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]] Awards,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/|title=Nominee List for 2017|publisher=[[National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]]|date=9 February 2018|accessdate=18 February 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180215172210/http://navgtr.org/archives/3351/|archive-date=15 February 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/|title=Horizon wins 7; Mario GOTY|publisher=National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers|date=13 March 2018|accessdate=14 March 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180314070824/http://navgtr.org/archives/3365/|archive-date=14 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> and for \"eSports Game of the Year\" at the 2018 [[SXSW Gaming Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|last=McNeill|first=Andrew|date=31 January 2018|url=https://gaming.sxsw.com/news/2018/2018-sxsw-gaming-awards-finalists/|title=Here Are Your 2018 SXSW Gaming Awards Finalists!|publisher=[[South by Southwest|SXSW]]|accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=IGN Studios|date=17 March 2018|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/03/18/sxsw-gaming-awards-2018-winners-revealed|title=2018 SXSW Gaming Awards Winners Revealed|website=[[IGN]]|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref> It won the award for \"Best Selling Game\" at the Italian Video Game Awards, whereas its other nomination was for \"People's Choice\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://italianvideogameawards.com/awards|title=Italian Video Game Nominees and Winners 2018|publisher=Italian Video Game Awards|date=14 March 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321193010/https://italianvideogameawards.com/awards|archivedate=21 March 2018|url-status=dead|accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref> It was also nominated for \"Best Game\" at [[BBC Radio 1|BBC Radio 1's Teen Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2018/radio-1s-teen-awards|title=Little Mix, 5 Seconds Of Summer, Sigrid and Jonas Blue lead the performances for BBC Radio 1's Teen Awards 2018|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=10 September 2018|accessdate=7 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Sales ===\nIn September 2018, EA Sports announced that the game sold more than 24 million with all of its versions.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Valentine |first1=Rebekah |title=FIFA 18 sells over 24 million copies |url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-09-05-fifa-18-sells-over-24-million-copies |website=Gamesindustry |accessdate=5 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Controversy ===\n''FIFA 18'' faced a backlash from fans due to its bugs and [[microtransaction]]s system in Ultimate Team mode which makes it [[pay-to-win]] resulting in a Black Friday boycott by fans in November 2017 and a petition being launched by fans with the [[hashtag]] #FixFifa. Players criticized EA of changing the game through patches which resulted in large amounts of glitches and bugs in the game, players not getting what they paid for, and the need to spend a large amount of real currency to obtain a decent Ultimate Team. FIFA Ultimate Team packs have been called [[loot box]]es in another name and the similarity to addictive gambling due to their use of variable-ratio scheduling used in gambling. Players also accused Ultimate Team packs of having mediocre drop rates. ''FIFA 18'', alongside several other EA games such as ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II (2017 video game)|Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'', are also under investigation by countries such as Belgium for their loot box systems.<ref>{{cite news|title=FIFA 18 Ultimate Team Microtransactions Cause Fan Uproar|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/11/23/fifa-18-ultimate-team-microtransactions-cause-fan-uproar|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=FIFA 18 fans organize Black Friday in-game purchase boycott|url=https://www.polygon.com/2017/11/23/16694776/fifa-18-fans-organize-black-friday-in-game-purchase-boycott|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Getting Rid of FIFA Ultimate Team packs Is the BestTthing EA Sports Can Do|url=https://www.dreamteamfc.com/c/gaming/360335/fifa-18-lootbox-release-ultimate-team/|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Micro Transactions System Used in FIFA Ultimate Team, Star Wars Battlefront and Other Popular Games Could Be Banned|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/gaming/micro-transactions-fifa-18-ultimate-team-star-wars-battlefront-banned-belgium-a8070106.html|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.easports.com/fifa}}\n*[https://200gaming.com/fifa-18-pc-game-download/ FIFA 18]\n\n\n{{Football video games by Electronic Arts}}\n{{Women's association football}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games|Association football|Women's association football}}\n\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Association football video games]]\n[[Category:Women's association football video games]]\n[[Category:EA Sports games]]\n[[Category:FIFA (video game series)]]\n[[Category:Frostbite (game engine) games]]\n[[Category:J.League licensed video games]]\n[[Category:La Liga licensed video games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Video games that support DirectX 12]]\n[[Category:Video games containing loot boxes]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in France]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in Germany]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in Italy]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Sports video games set in the United States]]\n[[Category:Sports video games with career mode]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Canada]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Romania]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch eShop games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 3 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 Pro enhanced games]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox 360 games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Diego Maradona]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Pel\u00e9]]\n[[Category:Works by Junkie XL]]\n", "name_user": "5.89.192.64", "label": "vandal", "comment": "(added soundtrack)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIFA_18"}
{"title_page": "Coming Forth by Day (album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Coming Forth by Day\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Cassandra Wilson]]\n| cover      = Coming Forth by Day - cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2015|4|6}}\n| recorded   = Summer 2014\n| venue      =\n| studio     = Seedy Underbelly Studios, Valley Village, CA\n| genre      = Jazz\n| length     = {{Duration|m=58|s=12}}\n| label      = [[Legacy Recordings]]\n| producer   = [[Nick Launay]]\n| prev_title = [[Another Country (Cassandra Wilson album)|Another Country]]\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\n'''''Coming Forth by Day''''' is a studio album by American jazz singer [[Cassandra Wilson]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fusilli|first1=Jim|title=Review of \u2018Coming Forth by Day\u2019 by Cassandra Wilson: Tribute Album as Birthday Present|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/review-of-coming-forth-by-day-by-cassandra-wilson-tribute-album-as-birthday-present-1428442383|website=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|publisher=wsj.com|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=7 April 2015}}</ref> The album was released on {{Start date|2015|4|6}} via [[Legacy Recordings]] label.\n\n==Background==\nThe album is a homage to legendary jazz vocalist [[Billie Holiday]] to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the singer's birth. The album includes 11 cover versions of famous [[jazz standards]] associated with Holiday and an original composition written by Cassandra Wilson\u2014\"Last Song (For Lester)\"\u2014imagined to be a heartbreaking final message from Holiday to her musical love, [[Lester Young]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Cassandra Wilson \u2013 Coming Forth by Day|url=https://www.discogs.com/Cassandra-Wilson-Coming-Forth-By-Day/release/7098865|website=[[Discogs]]|publisher=discogs.com|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Wilson explained: \"Coming Forth by Day is a homage dedicated to the beauty, power, and genius of Billie Holiday. A collection of musical spells, prescriptions for navigating the dubious myths surrounding her life and times, this record is a vehicle for the re-emergence of Billie\u2019s songbook in the 21st century.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Flynn |first1=Mike |title=Cassandra Wilson signs to Legacy Recordings for Billie Holiday tribute album |url=https://www.jazzwise.com/news/article/cassandra-wilson-signs-to-legacy-recordings-for-billie-holiday-tribute-album |website=[[Jazzwise]] |accessdate=16 March 2020 |language=en |date=13 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|title=Coming Forth by Day |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/coming-forth-by-day-mw0002817785|website=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2      = [[All About Jazz]]\n| rev2score = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last1=BAILEY|first1=C. MICHAEL|title=Cassandra Wilson: Cassandra Wilson: Coming Forth By Day|url=https://www.allaboutjazz.com/cassandra-wilson-coming-forth-by-day-by-c-michael-bailey.php|website=[[All About Jazz]]|publisher=allaboutjazz.com|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=April 21, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev3      = ''[[Elmore Magazine]]'' \n| rev3score = 86/100<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hynes|first1=Jim|title=Cassandra Wilson: Coming Forth By Day|url=http://www.elmoremagazine.com/2015/05/reviews/albums/cassandra-wilson|website=[[Elmore Magazine]]|publisher=elmoremagazine.com|accessdate=24 May 2018|date=May 26, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev4      = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev4score = 8/10<ref>{{cite web|last1=Doole|first1=Kerry|title=Cassandra Wilson Coming Forth|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/cassandra_wilson-coming_forth_by_day|website=[[Exclaim!]]|publisher=exclaim.ca|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=April 7, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev5      = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev5score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"TG\">{{cite news|last=Fordham|first=John|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/apr/09/cassandra-wilson-coming-forth-by-day-review|title=Cassandra Wilson: Another Country \u2013 review|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 April 2015|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref>\n| rev6       = [[laut.de]]\n| rev6score  = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brandstetter |first1=Markus |title=Neue Nuancen und Farben im US-amerikanischen Songbook. |url=https://www.laut.de/Cassandra-Wilson/Alben/Coming-Forth-By-Day-96238 |publisher=t.de]] |accessdate=17 September 2019 |language=de |date=3 April 2015}}</ref>\n| rev7       = ''[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]''\n| rev7score  = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shand |first1=John |title=Review: Rediscovering Billie Holiday's pain, genius and influence |url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/review-rediscovering-billie-holidays-pain-genius-and-influence-20150720-gifzm9.html |website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |accessdate=17 September 2019 |language=en |date=23 July 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n[[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] of [[AllMusic]] stated, \"Perhaps the pairing of Cassandra Wilson and Billie Holiday carries a whiff of inevitability, but there's nothing predictable about Coming Forth by Day. Released to coincide with Holiday's centennial in 2015, Coming Forth by Day explicitly celebrates Lady Day by drawing upon standards she sang in addition to songs she wrote, but Wilson deliberately sidesteps the conventional by hiring Nick Launay as a producer. As a result of his work with Nick Cave, Launay mastered a certain brand of spooky Americana, something that comes in handy with the Holiday catalog, but Coming Forth by Day is never too thick with murk. It luxuriates in its atmosphere, sometimes sliding into a groove suggesting smooth '70s soul, often handsomely evoking a cinematic torch song -- moods that complement each other and suggest Holiday's work without replicating it. This is a neat trick: such flexibility suggests how adaptable Holiday's songbook is while underscoring the imagination behind Wilson's interpretations. Certainly, Launay deserves credit for his painterly production, but the success of Coming Forth by Day belongs entirely to Wilson, who proves that she's an heir to Holiday's throne by never once imitating her idol.\"<ref name=\"AM\"/>\n\nChristopher Loudon of ''[[JazzTimes]]'' wrote, \"Though it\u2019s disheartening to realize that even an artist as eminent as Cassandra Wilson had to turn to [[PledgeMusic]] to fund her centenary salute to Billie Holiday, it\u2019s best to set aside such state-of-things ponderings and focus on the outcome. Which is, in a word, exquisite. It\u2019s also clever, insightful and, though utterly respectful to Holiday as source and touchstone, strikingly original.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Loudon|first1=Christopher|title=Cassandra Wilson: Coming Forth by Day|url=https://jazztimes.com/reviews/albums/cassandra-wilson-coming-forth-by-day/|website=[[JazzTimes]]|publisher=jazztimes.com|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=April 7, 2015}}</ref> Writing for ''[[DownBeat]]'', Bobby Reed commented, \"This disc, which includes 11 songs recorded by Billie Holiday, functions as an admirable tribute, but it doesn\u2019t sound like Lady Day. Wilson employs her own husky, occasionally hushed singing style, not attempting to re-create Holiday\u2019s famous vocal inflections\u2014and certainly not copying her arrangements. Instead, Wilson assembled a stellar, \u201coutside the box\u201d ensemble to interpret this material for a new generation of listeners.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Reed |first1=Bobby |title=Cassandra Wilson Coming Forth By Day (Legacy) |url=https://downbeat.com/reviews/detail/coming-forth-by-day |website=[[DownBeat]] |accessdate=16 March 2020 |date=April 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[John Fordham (jazz critic)|John Fordham]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' noted, \"Singer [[Jose James]]\u2019 recent tribute to Billie Holiday saw a fine singer and a hip jazz trio sprinkling personal magic on timeless songs with careful respect. Cassandra Wilson\u2019s angle on Holiday is very different: a radical, big-production remake of the great vocalist\u2019s music with the rhythm section from [[Nick Cave]]'s [[Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds|Bad Seeds]] giving the repertoire a thick-textured, abstract blues-rock feel, while a luxurious strings section embraces the ballads.\"<ref name=\"TG\"/> In his review for the ''[[Santa Barbara Independent]]'', Charles Donelan wrote, \"The album reveals yet another aspect of this visionary artist\u2019s immense talent, as Wilson ventures into the orchestral territory mapped out by Arcade Fire, with her sainted muse Billie Holiday by her side.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Donelan |first1=Charles |title=Cassandra Wilson |url=https://www.independent.com/2015/02/17/cassandra-wilson/ |website=[[The Santa Barbara Independent]] |accessdate=16 March 2020 |date=17 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = \n| headline  = \n| total_length = {{Duration|m=58|s=12}}\n\n| title1    = [[Don't Explain (song)|Don't Explain]]\n| writer1   = [[Arthur Herzog, Jr.]], [[Billie Holiday]]\n| length1   = 4:35\n\n| title2    = [[Billie's Blues]]\n| writer2   = [[Billie Holiday]]\n| length2   = 5:08\n\n| title3    = [[Crazy He Calls Me]]\n| writer3   = [[Carl Sigman]], [[Sidney Keith Russell]]\n| length3   = 6:19\n\n| title4    = [[You Go to My Head]]\n| writer4   = [[Haven Gillespie]], [[J. Fred Coots]]\n| length4   = 4:10\n\n| title5    = [[All of Me (jazz standard)|All of Me]]\n| writer5   = [[Gerald Marks]], [[Seymour Simons]]\n| length5   = 4:07\n\n| title6    = [[The Way You Look Tonight]]\n| writer6   = [[Dorothy Fields]], [[Jerome Kern]]\n| length6   = 3:51\n\n| title7    = [[Good Morning Heartache]]\n| writer7   = [[Dan Fisher (composer)|Dan Fisher]], [[Ervin Drake]], [[Irene Higginbotham]]\n| length7   = 4:57\n\n| title8    = [[What a Little Moonlight Can Do]]\n| writer8   = [[Harry M. Woods]]\n| length8   = 4:10\n\n| title9    = [[These Foolish Things]]\n| writer9   = [[Eric Maschwitz]], [[Jack Strachey]]\n| length9   = 4:14\n\n| title10   = [[Strange Fruit]]\n| writer10  = [[Lewis Allan]]\n| length10  = 4:55\n\n| title11   = [[I'll Be Seeing You (song)|I'll Be Seeing You]]\n| writer11  = [[Irving Kahal]], [[Sammy Fain]]\n| length11  = 6:10\n\n| title12   = Last Song (For Lester)\t\n| writer12  = Cassandra Wilson, [[Jon Cowherd]], [[Kevin Breit]], [[Martyn Casey]], Robby Marshall, [[Thomas Wydler]]\n| length12  = 5:51\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n* Cassandra Wilson \u2013 vocals, guitar\n* [[Kevin Breit]] \u2013 acoustic and electric guitar, banjo, loops\n* [[Jon Cowherd]] \u2013 piano, organ\n* [[Martyn P. Casey]] \u2013 bass\n* [[Thomas Wydler]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n* Robby Marshall \u2013 woodwinds, melodica\n* Ming Vauze - guitar string, Loops (1, 10, 12)\n* [[T Bone Burnett]] \u2013 baritone guitar (2, 4, 7)\n* [[Nick Zinner]] \u2013 additional guitar and loops (4, 8\u201310, 12) \n* [[Eric Gorfain]] \u2013 violin with echos (3, 5, 8, 10, 11), string arrangements (3, 5, 8, 10), notes extended (4)\n* [[The Section Quartet]] (Eric Gorfain, Daphne Chen, Lauren Chipman, Richard Dodd) - string quartet (3, 5, 8, 10)\n* [[Van Dyke Parks]] \u2013 string arrangements (4, 6)\n* Van Dyke Parks Orchestra (4, 6)\n'''Production'''\n* [[Nick Launay]] \u2013 producer, recording and mix, liner notes\n* Ed Gerrard - co-producer\n* Atom Greenspan - assistant producer and recording engineer\n* [[Bernie Grundman]] - mastering\n* Sherry Beth Mounce - project coordinator\n* Frank Harkins - art direction, design\n* [[Mark Seliger]] - photography\n\n==Chart performance==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Chart (2015)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n| US Jazz Albums (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|title=CASSANDRA WILSON: CHART HISTORY|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/cassandra-wilson/chart-history/jazz-albums|website=Billboard|publisher=[[billboard.com]]|accessdate=19 May 2019}}</ref>\n| align=center|1\n|- \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Cassandra Wilson}}\n\n[[Category:2015 albums]]\n[[Category:Cassandra Wilson albums]]\n[[Category:Legacy Recordings albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Nick Launay]]\n[[Category:Vocal jazz albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Coming Forth by Day\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Cassandra Wilson]]\n| cover      = Coming Forth by Day - cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2015|4|6}}\n| recorded   = Summer 2014\n| venue      =\n| studio     = Seedy Underbelly Studios, Valley Vaillage, CA\n| genre      = Jazz\n| length     = {{Duration|m=58|s=12}}\n| label      = [[Legacy Recordings]]\n| producer   = [[Nick Launay]]\n| prev_title = [[Another Country (Cassandra Wilson album)|Another Country]]\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\n'''''Coming Forth by Day''''' is a studio album by American jazz singer [[Cassandra Wilson]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fusilli|first1=Jim|title=Review of \u2018Coming Forth by Day\u2019 by Cassandra Wilson: Tribute Album as Birthday Present|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/review-of-coming-forth-by-day-by-cassandra-wilson-tribute-album-as-birthday-present-1428442383|website=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|publisher=wsj.com|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=7 April 2015}}</ref> The album was released on {{Start date|2015|4|6}} via [[Legacy Recordings]] label. \n\n==Background==\nThe album is a homage to legendary jazz vocalist [[Billie Holiday]] to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the singer's birth. The album includes 11 cover versions of famous [[jazz standards]] associated with Holiday and an original composition written by Cassandra Wilson\u2014\"Last Song (For Lester)\"\u2014imagined to be a heartbreaking final message from Holiday to her musical love, [[Lester Young]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Cassandra Wilson \u2013 Coming Forth by Day|url=https://www.discogs.com/Cassandra-Wilson-Coming-Forth-By-Day/release/7098865|website=[[Discogs]]|publisher=discogs.com|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> Wilson explained: \"Coming Forth by Day is a homage dedicated to the beauty, power, and genius of Billie Holiday. A collection of musical spells, prescriptions for navigating the dubious myths surrounding her life and times, this record is a vehicle for the re-emergence of Billie\u2019s songbook in the 21st century.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Flynn |first1=Mike |title=Cassandra Wilson signs to Legacy Recordings for Billie Holiday tribute album |url=https://www.jazzwise.com/news/article/cassandra-wilson-signs-to-legacy-recordings-for-billie-holiday-tribute-album |website=[[Jazzwise]] |accessdate=16 March 2020 |language=en |date=13 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|title=Coming Forth by Day |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/coming-forth-by-day-mw0002817785|website=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2      = [[All About Jazz]]\n| rev2score = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last1=BAILEY|first1=C. MICHAEL|title=Cassandra Wilson: Cassandra Wilson: Coming Forth By Day|url=https://www.allaboutjazz.com/cassandra-wilson-coming-forth-by-day-by-c-michael-bailey.php|website=[[All About Jazz]]|publisher=allaboutjazz.com|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=April 21, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev3      = ''[[Elmore Magazine]]'' \n| rev3score = 86/100<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hynes|first1=Jim|title=Cassandra Wilson: Coming Forth By Day|url=http://www.elmoremagazine.com/2015/05/reviews/albums/cassandra-wilson|website=[[Elmore Magazine]]|publisher=elmoremagazine.com|accessdate=24 May 2018|date=May 26, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev4      = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev4score = 8/10<ref>{{cite web|last1=Doole|first1=Kerry|title=Cassandra Wilson Coming Forth|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/cassandra_wilson-coming_forth_by_day|website=[[Exclaim!]]|publisher=exclaim.ca|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=April 7, 2015}}</ref>\n| rev5      = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev5score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"TG\">{{cite news|last=Fordham|first=John|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/apr/09/cassandra-wilson-coming-forth-by-day-review|title=Cassandra Wilson: Another Country \u2013 review|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 April 2015|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref>\n| rev6       = [[laut.de]]\n| rev6score  = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brandstetter |first1=Markus |title=Neue Nuancen und Farben im US-amerikanischen Songbook. |url=https://www.laut.de/Cassandra-Wilson/Alben/Coming-Forth-By-Day-96238 |publisher=t.de]] |accessdate=17 September 2019 |language=de |date=3 April 2015}}</ref>\n| rev7       = ''[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]''\n| rev7score  = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shand |first1=John |title=Review: Rediscovering Billie Holiday's pain, genius and influence |url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/review-rediscovering-billie-holidays-pain-genius-and-influence-20150720-gifzm9.html |website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |accessdate=17 September 2019 |language=en |date=23 July 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n[[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] of [[AllMusic]] stated, \"Perhaps the pairing of Cassandra Wilson and Billie Holiday carries a whiff of inevitability, but there's nothing predictable about Coming Forth by Day. Released to coincide with Holiday's centennial in 2015, Coming Forth by Day explicitly celebrates Lady Day by drawing upon standards she sang in addition to songs she wrote, but Wilson deliberately sidesteps the conventional by hiring Nick Launay as a producer. As a result of his work with Nick Cave, Launay mastered a certain brand of spooky Americana, something that comes in handy with the Holiday catalog, but Coming Forth by Day is never too thick with murk. It luxuriates in its atmosphere, sometimes sliding into a groove suggesting smooth '70s soul, often handsomely evoking a cinematic torch song -- moods that complement each other and suggest Holiday's work without replicating it. This is a neat trick: such flexibility suggests how adaptable Holiday's songbook is while underscoring the imagination behind Wilson's interpretations. Certainly, Launay deserves credit for his painterly production, but the success of Coming Forth by Day belongs entirely to Wilson, who proves that she's an heir to Holiday's throne by never once imitating her idol.\"<ref name=\"AM\"/>\n\nChristopher Loudon of ''[[JazzTimes]]'' wrote, \"Though it\u2019s disheartening to realize that even an artist as eminent as Cassandra Wilson had to turn to [[PledgeMusic]] to fund her centenary salute to Billie Holiday, it\u2019s best to set aside such state-of-things ponderings and focus on the outcome. Which is, in a word, exquisite. It\u2019s also clever, insightful and, though utterly respectful to Holiday as source and touchstone, strikingly original.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Loudon|first1=Christopher|title=Cassandra Wilson: Coming Forth by Day|url=https://jazztimes.com/reviews/albums/cassandra-wilson-coming-forth-by-day/|website=[[JazzTimes]]|publisher=jazztimes.com|accessdate=15 February 2018|date=April 7, 2015}}</ref> Writing for ''[[DownBeat]]'', Bobby Reed commented, \"This disc, which includes 11 songs recorded by Billie Holiday, functions as an admirable tribute, but it doesn\u2019t sound like Lady Day. Wilson employs her own husky, occasionally hushed singing style, not attempting to re-create Holiday\u2019s famous vocal inflections\u2014and certainly not copying her arrangements. Instead, Wilson assembled a stellar, \u201coutside the box\u201d ensemble to interpret this material for a new generation of listeners.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Reed |first1=Bobby |title=Cassandra Wilson Coming Forth By Day (Legacy) |url=https://downbeat.com/reviews/detail/coming-forth-by-day |website=[[DownBeat]] |accessdate=16 March 2020 |date=April 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[John Fordham (jazz critic)|John Fordham]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' noted, \"Singer [[Jose James]]\u2019 recent tribute to Billie Holiday saw a fine singer and a hip jazz trio sprinkling personal magic on timeless songs with careful respect. Cassandra Wilson\u2019s angle on Holiday is very different: a radical, big-production remake of the great vocalist\u2019s music with the rhythm section from [[Nick Cave]]\u2019s [[Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds|Bad Seeds]] giving the repertoire a thick-textured, abstract blues-rock feel, while a luxurious strings section embraces the ballads.\"<ref name=\"TG\"/> In his review for the ''[[Santa Barbara Independent]]'', Charles Donelan wrote, \"The album reveals yet another aspect of this visionary artist\u2019s immense talent, as Wilson ventures into the orchestral territory mapped out by Arcade Fire, with her sainted muse Billie Holiday by her side.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Donelan |first1=Charles |title=Cassandra Wilson |url=https://www.independent.com/2015/02/17/cassandra-wilson/ |website=[[The Santa Barbara Independent]] |accessdate=16 March 2020 |date=17 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = \n| headline  = \n| total_length = {{Duration|m=58|s=12}}\n\n| title1    = [[Don't Explain (song)|Don't Explain]]\n| writer1   = [[Arthur Herzog, Jr.]], [[Billie Holiday]]\n| length1   = 4:35\n\n| title2    = [[Billie's Blues]]\n| writer2   = [[Billie Holiday]]\n| length2   = 5:08\n\n| title3    = [[Crazy He Calls Me]]\n| writer3   = [[Carl Sigman]], [[Sidney Keith Russell]]\n| length3   = 6:19\n\n| title4    = [[You Go to My Head]]\n| writer4   = [[Haven Gillespie]], [[J. Fred Coots]]\n| length4   = 4:10\n\n| title5    = [[All of Me (jazz standard)|All of Me]]\n| writer5   = [[Gerald Marks]], [[Seymour Simons]]\n| length5   = 4:07\n\n| title6    = [[The Way You Look Tonight]]\n| writer6   = [[Dorothy Fields]], [[Jerome Kern]]\n| length6   = 3:51\n\n| title7    = [[Good Morning Heartache]]\n| writer7   = [[Dan Fisher (composer)|Dan Fisher]], [[Ervin Drake]], [[Irene Higginbotham]]\n| length7   = 4:57\n\n| title8    = [[What a Little Moonlight Can Do]]\n| writer8   = [[Harry M. Woods]]\n| length8   = 4:10\n\n| title9    = [[These Foolish Things]]\n| writer9   = [[Eric Maschwitz]], [[Jack Strachey]]\n| length9   = 4:14\n\n| title10   = [[Strange Fruit]]\n| writer10  = [[Lewis Allan]]\n| length10  = 4:55\n\n| title11   = [[I'll Be Seeing You (song)|I'll Be Seeing You]]\n| writer11  = [[Irving Kahal]], [[Sammy Fain]]\n| length11  = 6:10\n\n| title12   = Last Song (For Lester)\t\n| writer12  = Cassandra Wilson, [[Jon Cowherd]], [[Kevin Breit]], [[Martyn Casey]], Robby Marshall, [[Thomas Wydler]]\n| length12  = 5:51\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n* Cassandra Wilson \u2013 vocals, guitar\n* [[Kevin Breit]] \u2013 acoustic and electric guitar, banjo, loops\n* [[Jon Cowherd]] \u2013 piano, organ\n* [[Martyn P. Casey]] \u2013 bass\n* [[Thomas Wydler]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n* Robby Marshall \u2013 woodwinds, melodica\n* Ming Vauze - guitar string, Loops (1, 10, 12)\n* [[T Bone Burnett]] \u2013 baritone guitar (2, 4, 7)\n* [[Nick Zinner]] \u2013 additional guitar and loops (4, 8\u201310, 12) \n* [[Eric Gorfain]] \u2013 violin with echos (3, 5, 8, 10, 11), string arrangements (3, 5, 8, 10), notes extended (4)\n* [[The Section Quartet]] (Eric Gorfain, Daphne Chen, Lauren Chipman, Richard Dodd) - string quartet (3, 5, 8, 10)\n* [[Van Dyke Parks]] \u2013 string arrangements (4, 6)\n* Van Dyke Parks Orchestra (4, 6)\n'''Production'''\n* [[Nick Launay]] \u2013 producer, recording and mix, liner notes\n* Ed Gerrard - co-producer\n* Atom Greenspan - assistant producer and recording engineer\n* [[Bernie Grundman]] - mastering\n* Sherry Beth Mounce - project coordinator\n* Frank Harkins - art direction, design\n* [[Mark Seliger]] - photography\n\n==Chart performance==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Chart (2015)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n| US Jazz Albums (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|title=CASSANDRA WILSON: CHART HISTORY|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/cassandra-wilson/chart-history/jazz-albums|website=Billboard|publisher=[[billboard.com]]|accessdate=19 May 2019}}</ref>\n| align=center|1\n|- \n